paragraphs.title: week2.pdf, slide 34: Download the Data
paragraphs.text:
%sh
hadoop fs -rm /tmp/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz
wget http://kdd.ics.uci.edu/databases/kddcup99/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz \
-O /tmp/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz

paragraphs.title: week2.pdf slide 35: Load data in HDFS
paragraphs.text:
%sh
hadoop fs -put /tmp/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz /tmp
hadoop fs -ls -h /tmp/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz
rm  /tmp/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
input_file = "hdfs:///tmp/kddcup.data_10_percent.gz"
raw_rdd = sc.textFile(input_file)

paragraphs.title: week2.pdf slide 43: Importing local libraries
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pprint import pprint
csv_rdd = raw_rdd.map(lambda x: x.split(","))
head_rows = csv_rdd.take(5)
pprint(head_rows[0])

paragraphs.title: week2.pdf slide 44: Using non-lambda functions in transformation
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
def parse_interaction(line):
    elems = line.split(",")
    tag = elems[41]
    return (tag, elems)
key_csv_rdd = raw_rdd.map(parse_interaction)
head_rows = key_csv_rdd.take(5)
pprint(head_rows[0])

paragraphs.title: Completing the Analysis: Identify fields of interest.
Completing the Analysis: filter out the normal records
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
normal_raw_rdd = raw_rdd.filter(lambda x: 'normal.' in x)
attack_raw_rdd = raw_rdd.subtract(normal_raw_rdd)
attack_csv_rdd = attack_raw_rdd.map(lambda x: x.split(","))

paragraphs.title: Completing the Analysis: Creating a Data Frame [ based on Get Started/Hello World]
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

 row_data = attack_csv_rdd.map(lambda p: Row(
    app=p[41],
    duration=int(p[0]),
    protocol=p[1],
    service=p[2],
    flag=p[3],
    src_bytes=int(p[4]),
    dst_bytes=int(p[5])
    )
 )


attack_df = sqlContext.createDataFrame(row_data)
attack_df.registerTempTable("attacks")

leos_df.select(leos_df.app, leos_df.service).distinct().sort(leos_df["app"]).show()
